## 3. Tesseract.js v7 — Integration Gotchas

Tesseract.js v7 changed the worker API. Use this pattern in `src/services/inspection.js`:

```js
// LAZY LOAD pattern — import only when InspectionLab tab is opened, not at app startup
async function runOCR(imageInput, onProgress) {
  const { createWorker } = await import('tesseract.js');
  const worker = await createWorker('eng', 1, {
    // Explicit CDN paths prevent Vite asset bundling issues with WASM:
    workerPath: 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/tesseract.js@7.0.0/dist/worker.min.js',
    langPath: 'https://tessdata.projectnaptha.com/4.0.0',
    corePath: 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/tesseract.js-core@latest/',
    logger: m => { if (m.status === 'recognizing text') onProgress(Math.round(m.progress * 100)); }
  });
  const { data: { text } } = await worker.recognize(imageInput);
  await worker.terminate();
  return text;
}
```

- `optimizeDeps: { exclude: ['tesseract.js'] }` in vite.config.js prevents pre-bundle failure on WASM
- Progress bar: use `onProgress` callback to drive a `<progress value={pct} max={100}>` bar
- **Fallback trigger:** if `runOCR` throws OR takes >8s (setTimeout race), resolve with `SAMPLE_OCR_TEXT` instead; do NOT dead-end

