## 9. jsPDF + SheetJS Export Patterns

**jsPDF (4.2.1):**
```js
import jsPDF from 'jspdf';
const doc = new jsPDF({ orientation: 'landscape' });
doc.setFontSize(14);
doc.text('AgriPro — Dashboard Export', 14, 15);
// autoTable not needed: use manual doc.text() in a loop for data rows
doc.save('agripro-export.pdf');
```

**SheetJS (0.18.5 Apache-2.0):**
```js
import * as XLSX from 'xlsx';
const ws = XLSX.utils.json_to_sheet(dataArray);
const wb = XLSX.utils.book_new();
XLSX.utils.book_append_sheet(wb, ws, 'Report');
XLSX.writeFile(wb, 'agripro-export.xlsx');
```

No autotable plugin needed for jsPDF; manual text loop stays under the file budget and avoids an extra dep.

---

## 10. Recharts Chart Types by Role Dashboard

- Procurement: `<BarChart>` campaign volume procured vs target (one bar per campaign)
- Quality: `<PieChart>` inspection status distribution (Pass/Warn/Reject/Pending)
- Warehouse: `<BarChart>` bin fill rates (stacked: allocated vs capacity)
- Management: `<LineChart>` weekly inspection throughput trend + `<BarChart>` anomaly rate by crop

All Recharts components available in 3.9.0; no breaking changes from 2.x that affect these chart types.

---

## 11. Mobile Layout Notes (R13 hard requirement)

At `<768px`:
- Sidebar becomes bottom tab nav (5 icons, labels below)
- Main content: single column, stacked cards
- Inspection form: inputs stack full-width
- Pipeline bar: horizontal scroll or compact step dots
- OCR upload zone: full-width dropzone with large tap target

Test on `--width=390 --height=844` (iPhone 14) viewport in local Playwright pass.

